Description: Fragment of neck and flattened handle of a pottery transport amphora, gradual curve. Clay medium, orange-red; red inclusions. Circular stamp with sun symbol.
Excavator/field collector: Excavated by: Sir Charles Thomas Newton (?)
Curator's comments: The stamp is akin to that of the Rhodian eponym Timarchos, Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0220.29.
Acquisition name: Donated by: Egypt Exploration Fund (Trimming suggests the provenance)
